Package: seroCOP
Title: Correlates of Protection Analysis Using Bayesian Methods
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("David", "Hodgson", , "david.hodgson@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits generalized logistic functions to serological data (antibody titres)
    and infection outcomes using Bayesian methods implemented in Stan. Provides
    tools for assessing correlates of risk/protection including ROC AUC, LOO-CV,
    and Brier scores. Built around an R6 class for streamlined workflow.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://seroanalytics.org/seroCOP/
BugReports: https://github.com/seroanalytics/seroCOP/issues
